  <!-- Story -->
  <section id="story" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-4">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">A Character with a Story</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      First appearing in Kasing Lung’s illustrated fantasy world <em>The Monsters</em>, Labubu was imagined as a curious and slightly mischievous creature — sometimes bold, sometimes shy, always authentic. Through themed series like <strong>Forest Labubu</strong>, <strong>Starry Labubu</strong>, and <strong>Wizard Labubu</strong>, the character evolved into a multi‑dimensional symbol of emotion and imagination.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      At its heart, Labubu celebrates the imperfect joy of childhood. The exaggerated grin and bright, curious eyes invite us to embrace oddness, sincerity, and wonder — a small reminder that feeling deeply is a form of courage.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Series Guide -->
  <section id="series" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Series Guide — Themes & Notable Editions</h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Design Language</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Pointy ears, a wide mischievous smile, and a compact silhouette define Labubu’s core. Editions vary finishes (matte/gloss), palettes (pastel to vivid), and accessories (hats, capes, critters) while preserving an iconic shape.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Notable Lines</h4>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Seasonal series (Spring/Rainy Day/Sleepy)</li>
          <li>Fantasy series (Wizard/Starry/Forest)</li>
          <li>Event & collaboration editions</li>
          <li>Blind‑box surprises and chases</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Materials & Finish</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Durable PVC/ABS typical of designer toys; select runs feature flocking, translucent parts, or glitter finishes. Hand‑finished paint apps add subtle variation — each piece carries small nuances.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Care & Display</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Avoid direct sun and high humidity. Dust with a soft brush. For display, diffused light highlights sculpted contours; risers or mirror backs can enhance shelf presence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

