      <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">Why does my browser try to download instead of showing the page?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">If you upload a <code>.tsx</code> or <code>.jsx</code> file directly to GitHub Pages, it will be served as a static file — most browsers will download it instead of rendering. Use this <code>index.html</code> at the repository root so the site renders normally.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-4 mb-3">
      <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">Why doesn’t the 360° scene load on my site?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">Your host or the file host may block third‑party iframes (CSP/X‑Frame‑Options). Use the new‑tab link above or self‑host the HTML under the same domain.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-4 mb-3">
      <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">How do I care for flocked or translucent editions?</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">Avoid moisture and solvents. Use a soft, dry brush for flocking; microfiber for standard PVC/ABS surfaces.</p>
    </details>
